      <p>Hi Molly! We met briefly in Madison before your book talk at Kitchen Gallery. Thank you for coming and speaking &#8211; it was a lovely event and I loved reading the Zuni Cookbook, which you recommended.</p>
<p>You may have seen this in the New York Times, but I enjoyed this short piece on how gratitude can help combat impulse buys: <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/23/opinion/sunday/with-holiday-shopping-willpower-isnt-enough.html?_r=0" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/23/opinion/sunday/with-holiday-shopping-willpower-isnt-enough.html?_r=0</a></p>
<p>I don&#39;t buy a lot of things on impulse, but it made me wonder if practicing gratitude could also be a way to deal with the frustration that can come when you&#39;re on a budget and can&#39;t buy all the things you might want to have. </p>
<p>Feel better!</p>
