      <p>As someone currently experiencing her second cold in six weeks, I feel your pain. I believe in the healing powers of garlic soup, orange juice, hot lemon and ginger, satsumas, toast, BBC Pride and Prejudice, West Wing box sets and re-runs of Charmed. </p>
<p>I also comfort read when I&#39;m sick, so I&#39;m unlikely to read anything very much more taxing than last month&#39;s Vanity Fair, unless it creeps up on me while I&#39;m peeling a satsuma in my PJs. My favourite read of late though was (totally late to the party) Eleanor and Park by Rainbow Rowell. Not a taxing read, but so worth it. I wanted to re read it instantly.</p>
<p>I hope you&#39;re all speedily non-germy!</p>
